<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: PvP servers will become the main servers on EQ (response)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?WhiteWolf">WhiteWolf</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:53 a.m. 7/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: PvP servers will become the main servers on EQ (response)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=66" TARGET=_self>Re: PvP servers will become the main servers on EQ</A> (Oghma)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Actually, I could not disagree more with this statement. One of

<BR>&gt; the difficulties being PvP in EQ at this point is that there are
<BR>&gt; not enough PvP players to play against. Most players have stayed
<BR>&gt; PvE throughout the beta, and they are still having loads of fun.
<P>Exactly, "At this point." There isnt 16000 people playing Everquest yet. When you start hearing about the large scale wars that will be happening on the pvp server you will switch too. After all once you reach the level that lets you go everywhere and kill everything, what else is there to do? Nothing. And besides the reason that there arent enough PVP people is because it IS an option.
<P>&gt; There is just too much to do in EQ to ever get truly bored with
<BR>&gt; the game. When I get bored, it's because I've been hanging in
<BR>&gt; the same zone for too long, getting caught up in camping for
<BR>&gt; mobs or hunting in the same places all the time. All I need to
<BR>&gt; do is go to a new place, a new zone, and find new foes and new
<BR>&gt; ways of dyin.. er overcoming obstacles :).
<P>There is not too much in EQ to do that you will never get bored. The fact that it is NPC's you are fighting means that there is a point you will reach where you can kill everything and go everywhere and will not be able to do anything new because they dont change. I dont find sitting in the same area killing the same creature over and over again fun. No matter where you go or what zone you enter you do the same exact thing just with a different creature. I guarantee you most will get bored of it, just some faster than others.
<P>&gt; It's also possible that large scale quests will happen on all
<BR>&gt; the servers. There have been a couple in beta, and there will
<BR>&gt; definitely more, because all the participants have had a blast
<BR>&gt; doing them. This, btw, without requiring PvP status.
<P>The pvp quests will more than likely be more complex and more competative. You will have to fight your way to your goal and the prize will seem much greater because of what you have to go through to get it.
<P>&gt; I think you may be speaking from your own perspective, in that
<BR>&gt; YOU would leave if there were no human opponents or large scale
<BR>&gt; wars, and that's great! You know which style of play makes you
<BR>&gt; happy, and it's players like you that have pushed for the PvP
<BR>&gt; server you have now. A PvP server sounds like a great idea, and
<BR>&gt; I hope enough of you hop into it to keep it for final.
<P>I plan to be on the PVP server from day 1 through when the next game comes along.
<P>&gt; I can speak from my experience (and I have played EQ PvE and
<BR>&gt; PvP) that the PvE environment has plenty of excitement.
<P>Up to this point. You have not reached the level at which the NPC monsters are all too weak for you and you have nothing to kill for fun anymore. You can stay on the PvE server all you want... but when you do switch over to the PvP server and your level 1 and im level 50. Dont cry about not knowing that the PvP server was so fun and that it sucks that you are so far behind everyone else because I warned ya =)
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
